  "instructions": [
    "in a medium bowl, whisk together flour, smoked paprika, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper.",
    "in a large bowl, whisk together semi-skimmed milk, eggs, and grated cheddar cheese.",
    "add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and stir until just combined.",
    "add the softened butter and stir until the batter is smooth.",
    "fold in the chopped fresh parsley.",
    "pour the batter into a greased 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "place the smoked salmon fillet on top of the batter.",
    "bake in a preheated oven at 375 degrees fahrenheit for 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the dish comes out clean.",
    "remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
